P2 Badge Treat selector-only pytest runs as subset invocations

The launcher only disables the coverage floor when _has_test_paths() finds an on-disk path, so common subset selectors like -k, -m, or --lf still run with the global fail_under threshold from coverage config. This makes documented focused runs (for example python scripts/run_pytest.py -k test_foo) unexpectedly fail on coverage even when tests pass, which defeats the stated “iterate fast” behavior for subset runs.

